# 1. ドキドキ打ち合わせ！

???: Alright, once again...
Kawanishi: My name is Kawanishi of Happiness Home Research, and I'll be helping you find a nice property.
Minori: Thank you very much!
Kawanishi: So, getting right to the matter at hand... You're looking for a place you can base yourselves out of, yes?
Minori: Yes!
Minori: (Our very own place... The MORE MORE HOUSE...!)
Minori: MORE MORE HOUSE?!
Saito: Yes, it would be helpful to have a place for the group to call home moving forward.
Haruka: I agree. We just talked about all the trouble we've been running into booking meeting rooms...
Haruka: So, our new home could triple as one of those, a place for us to practice and a studio for our streams. We wouldn't have to spend as much time moving back and forth.
Airi: Hehe. See what I mean?
Airi: We've been so busy lately that time is really starting to come at a premium. I think it's worth considering this option.
Shizuku: Yes, I agree as well...! After all, we can only do so much up on the school's rooftop.
Minori: Y-Yeah, you all bring up good points. It would be really nice to have a place that sort of doubles as our home base...
Minori: But is this plan really possible? It's like us trying to rent our dream home!
Airi: Of course, we can't afford a lavish palace that's right next to a major terminal.
Airi: But we should be able to figure something out by discussing our wants and needs, and compromising where we can.
Haruka: Right... And because we've been getting steady work, we have a slightly bigger budget now.
Minori: Yeah...!
Saito: In any case, we should probably ask a realtor for further advice concerning this matter...
Saito: Since we're on a budget, I'll try to find a trustworthy agency that can still show us affordable options.
Saito: I'll need to stay here for a little while longer... But I'll let you all know once I've found a good one!
Minori: (I can't wait to see what kind of houses are available...)
Minori: (This is so exciting...!)
Kawanishi: I have documents on some potential candidates that we can look at together.
Kawanishi: Ms. Saito also already told me about your group's needs, so we can discuss those further and see what's going to be absolutely necessary.
Shizuku: What we're looking for is... A place with space for us to do our streams, practice and have meetings...
Kawanishi: Offices that are available for lease usually come up when I enter those things in...
Kawanishi: However, there was also mention that you'd prefer to have a shower. That made me consider more residential places as well.
Airi: Right. Not many of those kinds of offices have showers.
Minori: Wait, I'm having trouble imagining what a room where we'd practice dancing and stuff would look like in a regular house.
Kawanishi: The first property I'd like to have you all look at more or less covers that. Please tell me what you think...
Minori: Wow! This is amazing...! It's a plain old house, but the basement's all covered in mirrors like a dance studio!
Haruka: Not only that, it has all these sliding doors that allow you to cover them up. And this says it's even been soundproofed...
Airi: This looks incredible! We can definitely use it as a studio for practicing and streaming.
Kawanishi: Yes, and on the first floor, there's a spacious living room and a nice kitchen with an island.
Minori: An island?
Airi: Like the counters you see in the home ec room. That'll make it a lot easier to do cooking streams.
Shizuku: Yes, all we'd have to do is place the camera in the living room. Those streams would be like our own cooking program!
Haruka: By the way, what's this at the far end of the balcony...?
Kawanishi: Oh, that's an outdoor bath.
Minori: Th-There's an outdoor bath...?!
Kawanishi: It doesn't look very big based on this floor plan... But it should still be nice for when you want a change of pace.
Shizuku: I'm staggered... I wasn't expecting to hear about an outdoor bath.
Minori: M-Me neither... A kitchen with an island and an outdoor bath...
Minori: Imagine living in a place like this...
Haruka: Nice work with the stream, Minori. I decided to make you some salmon poke today to help you recharge. Let's eat our fill and do our best again tomorrow.
Haruka: You're done with your bath already, Minori? And your hair's still wet. Let me go get the dryer. I'd rather you didn't catch a cold.
Minori: Talk about living the dream. I'm not sure my heart would be able to handle it!
Haruka: Minori...
Airi: She's off in her own little world again...
Minori: Alright, I vote for this place! Where do we sign?!
Minori: I mean, it even said on that one website how you should pick a place you can imagine yourself living in!
Kawanishi: U-Uhh...
Airi: Calm down, will you? Yes, this place does have everything we need.
Airi: But we're on a budget. Take a look at the rent...
Minori: Huh? It costs...
Minori: I-It really costs this much...?
Kawanishi: Yes... This is a five-star property that fits your group's needs to the fullest.
Kawanishi: Now that you have this as a reference, we'll look at documents for these other properties...
Kawanishi: If any seem appealing to you, then I'll schedule us to go see them on a later date.
Minori: Oh, we get to see what they're actually like...?!
Haruka: Then, let's start looking at these one by one.
Minori: Okay!
Kawanishi: Thank you all for your time today.
Kawanishi: I'll start scheduling our visit for the properties we discussed.
Kawanishi: Also, I'll send another list of prospective candidates, so please let me know if you'd like to take a look at any of them.
Airi: Understood. Thank you very much for agreeing to meet with us today!
Kawanishi: Of course. I look forward to seeing you all again.
Minori: *Sigh* Browsing through all those papers was so much fun!
Haruka: Actually talking about this was pretty huge. Now we know that we prefer to have mirrors in the room where we plan on practicing, and that our stream studio doesn't have to be all that big.
Shizuku: Also, we learned that we can go without a kitchen island or an outdoor bath.
Airi: It would be nice to have those things, but I'm glad we're not choosing based on added luxuries.
Minori: Still, we get to see these places next time! I dunno if I can wait until then!
Airi: Again, slow down... We're getting another list of properties to look through, so this is far from over.
Minori: But... But... We might actually get to make the MORE MORE HOUSE a reality!
Minori: Then we could have sleepovers and stuff... How can I not be excited?!
Haruka: We get what you mean...
Airi: But don't forget that this is business. We're looking for a place to rent because we need one for work.
Minori: Oh, uh... Yeah, I know... This isn't all fun and games.
Minori: But it means we get to spend more time together. That makes me really happy...!
Airi: Oh, you...
Minori: Hehe...
Minori: (Choosing just one out of a big list isn't going to be easy... But we gotta pick the best place available to us to turn into the MORE MORE HOUSE!)
